comments: Daniels (NOP) brings his left hand toward Lowry's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs with Lowry's front as he drives inside the perimeter.
Nance Jr. (NOP) is stopping his forward momentum and marginal contact occurs with Lowry's (MIA) right arm and lower body as Lowry cuts back toward Nance Jr. after his gather.
Nance Jr. (NOP) and Adebayo (MIA) engage and disengage with one another as Adebayo moves to set the pick.
Nance Jr. (NOP) brings his arms toward Lowry's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs with Lowry's front and right arm prior to the start of his upward shooting motion.
Adebayo (MIA) engages and disengages with Nance Jr. (NOP) as Nance Jr. moves to set the pick.
Nance Jr. (NOP) establishes himself in Adebayo's (MIA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in Daniels' (NOP) path and does not deliver illegal contact as the defensive switch simultaneously occurs.
Nance Jr. (NOP) legally contests Lowry's (MIA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Daniels (NOP) grasps and then quickly releases Adebayo's (MIA) arm after the release of the jump shot attempt.
Murphy III (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Adebayo (MIA) prior to incidental arm contact occurring during the rebound.
Murphy III (NOP) and Adebayo (MIA) make incidental leg-to-leg contact with one another after the ball is dislodged away from Adebayo during the rebound.
Murphy III (NOP) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Oladipo's (MIA) upper body slightly extends to the side as he firms up over his right foot and he does not deliver illegal contact to Daniels (NOP) as the screen is set.
Murphy III (NOP) and Adebayo (MIA) engage and disengage with one another after the expiration of the pick.
Butler (MIA) brushes McCollum's (NOP) left arm and marginal contact occurs as McCollum spins back toward the middle of the floor.
Daniels (NOP) does not release the inbound (or request a timeout) within five seconds of being given the ball.
Murphy III (NOP) commits a take foul on Oladipo (MIA). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Daniels (NOP) and Butler (MIA) engage and disengage with one another after the release of the inbound pass.
Jones (NOP) and Herro (MIA) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Daniels (NOP) and Butler (MIA) each make clean contact with the ball and tie one another up as simultaneous incidental contact occurs. A jump ball is correctly assessed.
New Orleans signals for and is awarded the timeout after Valanciunas (NOP) gains full control of the jump ball while still inbounds.
Jones (NOP) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Butler (MIA) brushes McCollum's (NOP) left arm and marginal contact occurs as McCollum dribbles along the perimeter.
Butler (MIA) legally contests McCollum's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (NOP) commits a take foul on Oladipo (MIA).
Oladipo (MIA) legally contests Jones' (NOP) jump shot attempt.
